section.section:
"Anatomic pathology services" means:
Histopathology or surgical pathology;
Cytopathology;
Hematology;
Subcellular pathology and molecular pathology; or
Blood-banking services performed by pathologists.

text.section:
A clinical laboratory, a physician, or a group practice located in this State or in another state that provides anatomic pathology services for a patient in this State shall present, or cause to be presented, a claim, bill, or demand for payment for the services to:
Subject to the limitations of § 19-710(p) of the Health - General Article, the patient directly unless otherwise prohibited by law;
A responsible insurer or other third-party payor;
A hospital, public health clinic, or nonprofit health clinic ordering the services;
A referring laboratory;
On behalf of the patient, a governmental agency or its public or private agent, agency, or organization; or
A health care practitioner who orders but does not supervise or perform an anatomic pathology service on a Pap test specimen, provided the health care practitioner is in compliance with subsection (e)(2) of this section.
